    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Harvey</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 170.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 22, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatches Nos. 325, 326, 327, and
                            328, dated respectively March 12, March 18, March 28, and March 31, have
                            been received. Nos. 326, 327, and 328 have been submitted for perusal to
                            the Secretary of the Navy. Your proceedings relative to the rebel ram
                            Stonewall and the firing upon the United States frigate Niagara from
                            Castle Belem are approved.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James E. Harvey,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., Lisbon.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
